<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd0f9a6b3-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e" identifier="/us/usc/t50/s213"><num value="213">§ 213.</num><heading> Jurisdiction of confiscation proceedings</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Such prizes and capture shall be condemned in the district court of the United States having jurisdiction of the amount, or in admiralty in any district in which the same may be seized, or into which they may be taken and proceedings first instituted.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idd0f9a6b4-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">(R.S. § 5309; <ref href="/us/act/1877-02-27/ch69/s1">Feb. 27, 1877, ch. 69, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/19/253">19 Stat. 253</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s291">Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 291</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/36/1167">36 Stat. 1167</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idd0f9a6b5-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idd0f9a6b6-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idd0f9a6b7-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">R.S. § 5309 derived from <ref href="/us/act/1861-08-06/ch60/s2">act Aug. 6, 1861, ch. 60, § 2</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/12/319">12 Stat. 319</ref>.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Act <date date="1911-03-03">Mar. 3, 1911</date>, conferred the powers and duties of the former circuit courts upon the district courts.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idd0f9a6b8-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1877—Act <date date="1877-02-27">Feb. 27, 1877</date>, inserted “may” after “any district in which the same”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
